+# ADR-0001 — Test (and harden) the grants.gov normalization boundary
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-05-27
+- **Author:** Solution Architect (scheduled architecture review)
+- **Area:** `src/features/grant-ingest/grantsGov.ts`
+
+## Context
+
+Test coverage in this repo is uneven. The downstream heuristic scorer is
+well-covered (`scoring.test.ts`, 14 cases exercising each component), and
+most `features/*` modules ship `storage`/`validation`/`computation` tests.
+But the **ingestion normalization boundary** — `normalize`, `toNum`,
+`htmlToPlain` in `grantsGov.ts` — had **zero tests**.
+
+This is the highest-damage gap in the codebase. Every grant is shaped by
+`normalize` before it is stored (`grant-ingest/storage.ts`), and everything
+downstream is built on that stored shape: match scoring (`scoring.ts`),
+draft generation, deadline-radar, and the match certificates surfaced on the
+public `/verify` pages. The grants.gov Search2 API is explicitly described
+in-code as "loosely typed (fields come and go)" with "both string-encoded
+numbers and missing fields" — i.e. the input is hostile by nature and the
+normalization layer is the only thing standing between it and the whole
+product. A silent regression here corrupts data nothing downstream can
+recover.
+
+Inspecting the boundary against its own documented invariants surfaced two
+**pre-existing defects**, both now pinned by tests:
+
+1. **Non-deterministic id fallback** (`grantsGov.ts`). For a payload missing
+   both `id` and `number`, the id was `${agencyCode}-${Math.random()...}`.
+   Storage uses `id TEXT PRIMARY KEY` with `ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE`
+   (`storage.ts:14,61`). A random id never collides, so re-ingesting the same
+   grant **inserts a duplicate row on every run** instead of upserting —
+   inflating match lists with phantom duplicates over time.
+2. **`toNum` returns `0` for junk strings.** `"not a number".replace(/[^0-9.-]/g,"")`
+   yields `""`, and `Number("")` is `0` (finite), so unparseable award fields
+   became a **$0 award** rather than "unknown" (`null`). A $0 floor/ceiling
+   feeds the award-size sweet-spot scorer as real data, distorting fit scores.
+
+## Decision
+
+1. **Establish unit-test coverage for the normalization boundary.** Export
+   `normalize`, `toNum`, `htmlToPlain` and add `grantsGov.test.ts` (21 cases)
+   covering the field coercions and the invariants downstream relies on:
+   string/`"none"`/junk number coercion, the id fallback chain and its
+   stability, the agency/cfdaList scalar-vs-array fallbacks, default values,
+   `rawJson` round-trip, and HTML/entity stripping for mission scoring.
+   Network fetching stays out of scope — these are pure functions.
+2. **Fix the two defects the tests exposed**, aligning the code with its
+   documented intent:
+   - `id` fallback now uses a deterministic content hash (`stableHash`), so
+     identical payloads map to identical ids and upserts collide as designed.
+   - `toNum` now requires at least one digit in the cleaned string before
+     parsing, returning `null` (unknown) for junk instead of `0`.
+
+This judges against the architecture that exists (pure-function feature
+modules, per-feature tests, SQLite stepping-stone with stable storage API)
+rather than reaching for an integration harness the scaffold doesn't need yet.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- **Positive:** The data front door now has regression coverage; the two
+  fixed defects no longer silently corrupt the grants table or fit scores.
+  Full suite green: 18 files / 194 tests (was 173; +21). No new dependencies,
+  no API change for callers (only added `export`s).
+- **Negative / trade-offs:** `stableHash` is a non-cryptographic rolling hash
+  (collisions theoretically possible across genuinely different id-less
+  payloads); acceptable because such payloads are rare and a collision merely
+  merges two amount-less rows. The `htmlToPlain` entity table is a hand-rolled
+  allowlist (`&amp; &lt; &gt; &quot; &#39;`); exotic entities pass through as
+  raw text — fine for keyword scoring, revisit if synopsis text is ever shown
+  verbatim in the UI.
+- **Still uncovered (follow-up):** the network fetch paths
+  (`fetchOpportunities`, `fetchOpportunityDetail`) and the `getMatches` DB
+  entry point. Tracked below; not blocking.
+
+## Task breakdown — 5 tasks, 9 story points
+
+| # | Task | Scope | Pts |
+|---|------|-------|-----|
+| 1 | Pin normalization boundary | Export + `grantsGov.test.ts` (21 cases) — **done this run** | 3 |
+| 2 | Fix non-deterministic id fallback | Deterministic `stableHash` so upserts collide — **done this run** | 1 |
+| 3 | Fix `toNum` junk→$0 | Require a digit; junk → `null` — **done this run** | 1 |
+| 4 | Cover network fetch paths | `vi.fn()`-mock `fetch`: HTTP-error throw, `errorcode!=0` throw, empty `oppHits`, detail `synopsis` missing | 2 |
+| 5 | Cover `getMatches` DB entry point | In-memory sqlite (`:memory:`) + `migrate`; assert empty-DB `[]`, ordering, `limit`, `GrantMatch` shape | 2 |
+
+Tasks 1–3 are delivered in this run (5 pts). Tasks 4–5 (4 pts) are scoped for
+a delivery agent.
+

